The paper presents an approach for solving driver behavior at the macroscopic scale, which involves modeling traffic flow and making decisions at interfaces using local information. This suggests that the paper could fall under the categories of systems and control (cs.SY), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computer engineering (cs.CE). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of traffic models, which could place it under the categories of information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG).
